---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure"
  description="Full disclosure of our affiliate relationships. We earn commissions on some of the services we recommend — at no additional cost to readers."
>
  <section class="container-article py-12 md:py-16">
    <h1 class="font-heading font-extrabold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-slate-deep tracking-tight">
      Affiliate disclosure.
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mt-6">
      <p>
        The Yard Scout participates in affiliate programs from several manufacturers and retailers
        of hot tub, sauna, and cold plunge equipment. When you click a link on this site and buy
        through one of those programs, we may earn a commission at <strong>no additional cost to
        you</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>Brands with active affiliate relationships</h2>
      <p>As of the current publication, we hold or are pursuing affiliate relationships with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Plunge — premium cold plunge tubs</li>
        <li>The Cold Plunge — premium cold plunge tubs</li>
        <li>Cold Plunge Co — mid-tier cold plunge</li>
        <li>Almost Heaven Saunas — barrel and traditional saunas (via ShareASale)</li>
        <li>Clearlight — premium infrared saunas</li>
        <li>Sun Home Saunas — mid-tier infrared</li>
        <li>Sunlighten — premium infrared</li>
        <li>Bestway / SaluSpa / Coleman — inflatable hot tubs (via Amazon Associates)</li>
        <li>Intex — inflatable hot tubs (via Amazon Associates)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How affiliate links are marked</h2>
      <p>
        All outbound links to affiliate partners are marked with <code>rel="sponsored"</code> in the
        HTML, which is the standard signal Google requests for affiliate links. They open in a new
        tab.
      </p>

      <h2>How recommendations are ranked</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>We rank by operator usability, not commission size.</strong> If two services offer
        similar features but one pays us a $30 commission and another pays $80, we'll still
        recommend whichever is better for the landlord reading our article.
      </p>
      <p>
        For example: a higher-AOV premium cold plunge with a $200 commission may not be the right
        recommendation for a beginner — sometimes a $300 chest-freezer DIY build is the better
        starting point even though it earns us nothing. Our reviews reflect that — we recommend
        what fits, even when other choices would pay us more.
      </p>

      <h2>What this affiliate revenue funds</h2>
      <p>
        Affiliate commissions fund the editorial and research work behind this site. We don't run
        paid advertising or sponsored content.
      </p>

      <h2>FTC compliance</h2>
      <p>
        This disclosure exists in compliance with the U.S. Federal Trade Commission's "Guides
        Concerning the Use of Endorsements and Testimonials in Advertising" (16 CFR Part 255).
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about how we handle affiliate relationships,{" "}
        <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
